    "en": {
      "title": "Kota is coming back to Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Indian media have reported that former Sri Lankan President Gotabaya Rajapaksa will return to Colombo next Wednesday (24).",
        "He fled the country following the anti-people protest held on July 9 and resigned from his presidency.",
        "He went to Maldives from Sri Lanka and from there went to Singapore and now he has taken refuge in Thailand.",
        "It is mentioned in the news that the Thai government has announced that Gotabaya has only been granted permission to stay temporarily on humanitarian grounds and cannot stay permanently.",
        "It has been reported that various restrictions have been imposed on him in Thailand and that he has been placed under house arrest for security reasons.",
        "In this case, former President Kota's wife Anoma Rajapaksa has American citizenship, so it is reported that Kota is eligible to get American citizenship again as her husband.",
        "It has also been reported that his legal experts in the United States are carrying out the procedures for this.",
        "It is noteworthy that Kota, who acquired US citizenship in 2003, revoked his US citizenship when he contested the 2019 presidential election.",
        "Meanwhile, it is also worth noting that the Inspector General of Police has ordered to increase the security arrangements at the house of former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa in Mirihana Pengrivat and the surrounding area."
      ],
